│ block 'exit.peel.next' that branches to 'loop.header.peel.next', which then branches to 'exit'. However, the original exit block 'exit' is still present  │
│ but is no longer reachable from the main loop because the loop latch now branches to 'exit.peel.begin' instead of 'exit'. The problem is that when there  │
│ are no PHIs in the exit block (ExitValues is empty), the code still calls formLCSSA(*L, DT, LI, SE) at line 1218, which may be creating unnecessary LCSSA │
