│ The exit block 'exit' has no PHIs (as confirmed by our debugging), so ExitValues is empty. The transformation creates new blocks 'exit.peel.begin',       │
│ 'loop.header.peel', etc., but the original exit block becomes unreachable. The formLCSSA call is executed regardless of whether there are any exit values │
│ to process.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The root cause is that formLCSSA is being called unconditionally when PeelLast=true, even when there are no PHI    │
│ nodes in the exit block that need to be updated. The formLCSSA function ensures that all values live out of the loop are represented by LCSSA PHI nodes,  │
│ but when there are no such values (no PHIs in exit blocks), this call is unnecessary and may be interfering with the control flow structure. In this      │
│ specific case, since the exit block has no PHIs, calling formLCSSA is not needed and may be causing the dominator tree or other analyses to become        │
│ inconsistent, leading to the unreachable exit block.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): The fix is to only call formLCSSA when there are actually exit values  │
